For small areas (like a pot on the patio), try cherry tomatoes. You may be surprised at how well they do in your pot and how sweet they taste in salads and off the vine. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fa/Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/fa/Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/aid2070318-v4-728px-Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For an old-fashioned, classic taste, try heirlooms such as Brandywine, Black Krum, or more. These have a delicious taste and do well in almost anything, but can be more susceptible to disease than hybrids. These do best in a larger area. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/63/Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/aid2070318-v4-728px-Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For giant kinds, try Big Boy and/or Beefsteak. These kinds take up a lot of space and if you want them to be big, you should prune some of the tomatoes off it so it focuses on making them bigger, not making more. These kinds can attempt to overgrow your garden, so be aware! They taste best in sandwiches and sometimes salads. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b7/Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b7/Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/aid2070318-v4-728px-Pick-the-Right-Tomato-Plant-for-Your-Garden-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
